steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"4cnj1","text":"Depending on cell type, collect the cells by scrapping them with a scrapper in Dulbecco’s Phosphate Buffered saline modified without calcium chloride and magnesium chloride (DPBS) (SH-SY5Y) or, using 0.25% Trypsin-EDTA (HMEC-1) for which stop enzymatic reaction by adding culture medium.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3d5e4","text":"Centrifuge cell suspensions at 450 g (SH-SY5Y) or 2500 rpm (HMEC-1), 4°C for  .","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":77,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"231uj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"duration","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"duration":300,"guid":"79C2AB90724E11EDA2F4CFEC87AA77E3","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null}}}}
